Earlier this week, angry residents blocked the roads with burning tyres and burned some municipality properties, including the mayor's car over electricity tariff hikes. JOHANNESBURG - Major roads were reopened to traffic in the Bela-Bela area on Saturday following a week long protest which claimed one life.Earlier this week, angry residents blocked the roads with burning tyres and burned some municipality properties, including the mayor's car over electricity tariff hikes.An 11-year-old boy died after being struck in the head by a rubber bullet during a standoff with the police.Local mayor Jeremiah Ngobeni said all services would fully operational by Monday. We have informed the community that we ll do collections, even in areas where we have not collected. 